> A single-wire sensor will have to be mounted in the heater box in order
> to ensure it gets heated to the correct temperature, but a more
> expensive heated sensor can be mounted in the tailpipe if you prefer
> not to drill the heater box pipe.

The best place to mount the O2 sensor is the "earliest" point in the exhaust
system where the O2 sensor can "see" the combined exhaust of the two heads.
In any case, it certainly should go *in front* of any catalytic converter so
that it's acting on the "unmodified" exhaust.
